      "term": "Second Middle Passage",
      "definition": "More than 2 million slaves were sold between 1820 and 1860, a majority to local buyers but hundreds of thousands from older states to \"importing\" states of the Lower South, resulting in what came to be known as the Second Middle Passage.",
